 Lady Frere - Lady Frere police have appealed to the public for assistance with information that can help them locate a missing 30-year-old woman. She is from Zakhele location in Lady Frere. According to police spokesperson, Captain Namhla Mdleleni, Asavela Hangana was last seen by her friend in her flat on the 22 October 2019, at about 18:30. "Her friend went to check on her the following day - 23 October 2019, and she was not there," Capt Mdleleni said. "Police were summoned and missing person docket was opened. "Anyone who  can assist to find Asavela can please. Contact. LT Colonel Mazwi at 0824418358 or 0860010111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 